Hello Kimberly and Emily,=20
I agree that the Euro provisions should be separated from the other group o=
f proposed annexes to the protocol because the Euro subject matter relates =
to practical issues which must be addressed by the Jan. 1 deadline.  The ma=
jority of the other annexes relate to substantive and material changes to t=
he way many existing provisions of the 1992 Master Agreement work (except f=
or, among other things, the Force Majeure provisions which are mostly not a=
ddressed in the 1992 Master Agreement. . . . . a possible reason for separa=
ting the Force Majeure annex from the rest).  As far as the annexes which w=
ould make substantive changes to current provisions of the 1992 agreement, =
I understand from your email that ISDA is now proposing to role them into a=
 "new" master agreement rather than issuing them in protocol form.  Would i=
t not be a good litmus test to judge the acceptance by the ISDA membership =
(and otherwise) of each of the proposed annexes by issuing them in protocol=
 form in order to see who and how many sign up for them?
Thank you.=20
